Not so much!  Stingy portions and TERRIBLE sauces. Ok first the good news, the goat tacos and the queso fundido were very good although the queso was 50% sausage.  Good sausage but it competed with the tasty baked/melted queso.  The bad news: Contrary to some reviews I read, (maybe the night I went , it was a different cook) were TINY!  The namesake guacamole was about a half a cup at most; the tacos, although tasty, where also very small one the smallest tortillas, I've ever seen.  But the thing that pissed me off the most was that they served up about 15 tortilla chips that fit in a little metal cup!  When I asked for more, the waiter told me I'd have to pay extra!!  And then the next offensive thing were the sauces.  First, there were no sauces, well, only a teeny green yucky one,  on the table, I had to ask for some red sauce for the chips.  They brought me some about the size of one of those containers that you get when you have to serve yourself your own ketchup - I'd say about 1ounce's worth-and it was THE WORST tasting stuff I've ever had.  ....and I'm old!! I've been to a LOT of Mexican restaurants. lol  I kept asking for some other type of sauce hoping I might find one that was better-green, red and finally this "hot" sauce that was made with liquid smoke-I swear, I know that smell and flavor very well.  Margaritas weren't great but I did appreciate that at least they weren't sickening sweet as they are in some restaurants.  Other good news, the waiters were nice and attentive and the decor is very nice and a fun mix of families and young couples.  But ultimately, I won't be going there again unless I'm in the mood for goat tacos and nothing else.

As for most Mexican restaurants that don't explicitly state otherwise , their rice and retries beans are not vegetarian , which makes it harder to order a vegetarian meal here.  They do have several vegetarian options but you have to make sure to tell them not to include rice or retries beans.  This is a great place to get Mexican food, especially if you have no dietary restrictions. If you are vegetarian, you are better off going someplace with more options.
